The paper proposes a method for learning CNN-based semantic segmentation models, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of different types of annotations for training, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The proposed method involves the use of deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on benchmark datasets, which involves performance evaluation, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of diverse training data, which can also be related to information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category.
